Field.Name: MENTTitle
Field.PromptText: MENTAL HEALTH SURVEY

Field.Name: N1DrinksLabel
Field.PromptText: 1. One drink is equivalent to a 12-ounce beer, a 5-ounce glass of wine, or a drink with one shot of liquor. During the last 30 days, on the days when you drank, about how many drinks did you drink on the average?

Field.Name: DrinkDays
Field.PromptText: No. of Days

Field.Name: NumDrinks
Field.PromptText: No. of Drinks

Field.Name: DontKnow
Field.PromptText: Don't Know

Field.Name: DrnkCompare
Field.PromptText: 2. Are you currently drinking MORE than you drank in the 12 months before the oil spill, LESS, or ABOUT THE SAME as in the 12 months before the oil spill?

Field.Name: Label2
Field.PromptText: INTERVIEWER: Now I am going to ask you some questions about some feelings that you have had in the past 30 days so that we can understand more about this type of work for the future. Please answer: All the time, Most of the time, Sometimes, Rarely or Never.

Field.Name: N3Sleep
Field.PromptText: 3. In the past 30 days, how often was your sleep restless?

Field.Name: N4Fear
Field.PromptText: 4. During the past 30 days, how often did you feel fearful?

Field.Name: N5Hope
Field.PromptText: 5. During the past 30 days, how often did you feel hopeful about the future?

Field.Name: N6Lonely
Field.PromptText: 6. During the past 30 days, how often did you feel lonely?

Field.Name: N7Focus
Field.PromptText: 7. During the past 30 days, how often did you have trouble keeping your mind on what you were doing?

Field.Name: N8Sad
Field.PromptText: 8. During the past 30 days, how often did you feel sad or depressed?

Field.Name: N9Effort
Field.PromptText: 9. During the past 30 days, how often did you feel that everything you did was an effort?

Field.Name: N10Bother
Field.PromptText: 10. During the past 30 days, how often did you feel bothered by things that usually don't bother you?

Field.Name: N11Angry
Field.PromptText: 11. During the past 30 days, how often have you felt so angry that you either lost your temper or felt out of control?

Field.Name: N12Happy
Field.PromptText: 12. During the past 30 days, how often did you feel happy?

Field.Name: N13Going
Field.PromptText: 13. During the past 30 days, how often did you feel that you could not get "going?"

Field.Name: N14future
Field.PromptText: 14. During the past 30 days, how much have you worried about your future physical health as a result of working on the oil spill?

Field.Name: Proceed
Field.PromptText: Proceed to Page 2

Field.Name: N16FGo4Help
Field.PromptText: 16. People differ a lot in their feelings about professional help for mental health problems. If you had a SERIOUS mental health problem, would you DEFINITELY go for professional help, PROBABLY go, PROBABLY NOT go, or DEFINITELY NOT go for professional help?

Field.Name: N17Access
Field.PromptText: 17. Do you have access to professional help for mental health concerns if desired?

Field.Name: N15Angry

Field.Name: N17Access1
